## Backend (Node.js + Express + MongoDB)

### Server: [backend/server.js](file:///c:/Users/khush/OneDrive/Desktop/ecommerce/backend/server.js)
- Helmet (security headers)
- CORS (frontend URL whitelist)
- Rate limiting (200 req/15min globally, 10 req/min for auth)
- Morgan logging
- Raw body for Stripe webhooks

### Models
| Model | Key Fields |
|-------|-----------|
| User | name, email, password (bcrypt), role, addresses[], refreshTokens[] |
| Product | title, slug, images[], price, compareAtPrice, categories[], tags[], inventory, variants[], badge, rating, featured |
| Order | user ref, items[], shippingAddress, paymentIntentId, paymentStatus, status, subtotal/tax/total |
| Review | product+user refs, rating 1-5, comment, verified, unique per user+product |

### API Routes
| Route File | Endpoints |
|-----------|-----------|
| auth.js | POST register, login, refresh, logout |
| products.js | GET list (filter/sort/paginate/search), GET by slug, POST/PUT/DELETE (admin) |
| cart.js | GET, POST add/update, DELETE item, DELETE all (JWT protected) |
| orders.js | POST create+Stripe PaymentIntent, GET list, GET by ID |
| users.js | GET me, PUT me, POST address, DELETE address |
| admin.js | GET dashboard stats, GET/PUT orders, GET users, PUT user role |
| webhook.js | POST Stripe events (payment_intent.succeeded/failed) |

### Security
- JWT access tokens (15min) + rotating refresh tokens (7 days)
- bcrypt password hashing (salt rounds: 12)
- Rate limiting on all routes + stricter limits on auth
- Helmet headers, CORS whitelist
- Centralized error handler (Mongoose validation, duplicate key, CastError, JWT)

